Tutorial
========

The configuration file
----------------------

Configuration of the problem.

Parameters
----------
r : float
    Nanoparticle radius. [r] = nm
R_Forster : float
    Forster radius. [R_Forster] = nm
L_D : float
    Length  of exciton diffusion. [L_D] = nm
tau_D : float
    Lifetime of donor. [tau_D] = ns
num_acceptors : float
    Number of acceptors in the nanoparticle.
delta_t : float
    Time interval. [delta_t] ) ns
num_exc : float
    Numbers of exitation of the same nanoparticle
acceptors : str, optional
    Way to create the acceptors. Can be 'vol' (volumetrically) for uniform distribution inside of nanoparticle or 'sup' (superficialy)  for uniform distributions on the surface of the nanoparticle.
    The default options is 'vol'.
exiton : str, optional
    Way to create the exetion. Can be 'laser' to generate uniformily in the nanoparticle or 'elec' (electrolysis) to generate between the radius R of the nanoparticle and a r (R > r).
    The default options is 'laser'.


